---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import { DOMAIN } from '../../data/site';

const title = "How to Calculate Maintenance Calories - Metabolic Adaptation Guide | BodyCompOS";
const description = "Learn how to establish your baseline maintenance calories (TDEE) and understand the impact of metabolic adaptation and adaptive thermogenesis.";
const canonical = `${DOMAIN}/guides/maintenance-calories`;

const schema = {
	'@context': 'https://schema.org',
	'@type': 'Article',
	headline: title,
	description: description,
	datePublished: '2026-06-25',
	dateModified: '2026-06-25',
	author: {
		'@type': 'Organization',
		name: 'BodyCompOS Editorial Board',
	},
	publisher: {
		'@type': 'Organization',
		name: 'BodyCompOS',
		logo: {
			'@type': 'ImageObject',
			url: `${DOMAIN}/favicon.svg`,
		},
	},
};
---

<Layout title={title} description={description} canonical={canonical} schema={[schema]}>
	<section class="site-container py-10 sm:py-12">
		<!-- Breadcrumbs -->
		<nav class="flex mb-6 text-xs font-semibold text-muted-foreground gap-2" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
			<a class="hover:text-accent transition-colors" href="/">Home</a>
			<span>/</span>
			<a class="hover:text-accent transition-colors" href="/guides">Guides</a>
			<span>/</span>
			<span class="text-foreground">Maintenance Calories Guide</span>
		</nav>

		<!-- Content Hero -->
		<div class="max-w-3xl">
			<p class="eyebrow">Metabolic Science</p>
			<h1 class="mt-3 text-4xl font-black leading-tight sm:text-5xl text-foreground">
				How to Calculate Maintenance Calories <br/>
				<span class="text-accent bg-gradient-to-r from-accent to-success bg-clip-text text-transparent">Metabolic Adaptation & Baseline TDEE</span>
			</h1>
			<p class="mt-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-muted-foreground">
				Maintenance calories represent the daily energy intake needed to maintain your body weight. This guide explains how to calculate your maintenance baseline, adjust for activity levels, and manage metabolic adaptation.
			</p>
		</div>

		<!-- Main editorial body -->
		<div class="mt-10 max-w-4xl grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[1fr_300px]">
			<div class="content-panel bg-card border border-border p-6 sm:p-8 rounded-2xl">
				<div class="prose-lite space-y-8 text-sm text-muted-foreground leading-relaxed">
					
					<section>
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mb-3">1. Understanding Maintenance Energy</h2>
						<p>
							Your maintenance calories, or Total Daily Energy Expenditure (TDEE), is the total energy required to support baseline metabolic functions and daily activity. When your daily energy intake matches your TDEE, you are in energy balance, and body weight remains stable.
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3">
							TDEE is calculated by multiplying your Basal Metabolic Rate (BMR)—the energy burned at complete rest—by an activity multiplier that represents your daily movement and exercise.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mb-3">2. Mathematical Estimations</h2>
						<p>
							The Mifflin-St Jeor equation (Mifflin et al., 1990) is the standard formula for estimating resting metabolism (BMR):
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3 font-semibold text-foreground">For Males:</p>
						<p class="font-mono bg-muted/40 p-3 rounded-lg text-xs">
							BMR = 10 * Weight (kg) + 6.25 * Height (cm) - 5 * Age (years) + 5
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3 font-semibold text-foreground">For Females:</p>
						<p class="font-mono bg-muted/40 p-3 rounded-lg text-xs">
							BMR = 10 * Weight (kg) + 6.25 * Height (cm) - 5 * Age (years) - 161
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3">
							For individuals with low body fat or significant muscle mass, the Katch-McArdle formula provides a more customized estimate by focusing on fat-free mass (FFM):
						</p>
						<p class="font-mono bg-muted/40 p-3 rounded-lg text-xs">
							BMR = 370 + 21.6 * Lean Body Mass (kg)
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mb-3">3. The Reality of Metabolic Adaptation</h2>
						<p>
							Maintenance calories are not static. During a prolonged calorie deficit, your body undergoes **metabolic adaptation** (or adaptive thermogenesis). This process reduces your energy expenditure to defend stored energy reserves. 
						</p>
						<p class="mt-3">
							BMR declines as body mass decreases, and Non-Exercise Activity Thermogenesis (NEAT) often drops unconsciously (e.g., fewer fidgeting movements and lower general activity) to conserve energy. This adaptation can reduce TDEE by up to 10% to 15% beyond what is expected from weight loss alone. This is why our forecasting engine applies a compounding weekly decay pacing factor (0.96 per month) to weight-loss projections.
						</p>
					</section>

					<section>
						<h2 class="text-xl font-bold text-foreground mb-3">4. Reassessment and Verification</h2>
						<p>
							Because formulas are population estimates, verify your calculated maintenance calorie targets by tracking your weight and food intake under consistent conditions for 2 to 4 weeks. If body weight remains stable, your actual intake matches your maintenance calories. If weight shifts, adjust your targets in 100-150 kcal increments.
						</p>
					</section>

					<!-- YMYL Disclaimer -->
					<div class="border-t border-border pt-6 text-[10px] text-muted-foreground">
						<p><strong>YMYL Disclaimer:</strong> This guide is for educational purposes only. Daily caloric expenditures are estimated and can vary based on individual thyroid function, health conditions, and activity. Consult a qualified metabolic health professional for clinical dietary support.</p>
					</div>

				</div>
			</div>
			
			<!-- Sidebar -->
			<div class="space-y-6">
				<div class="surface border border-border p-5 rounded-2xl">
					<h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-foreground">Strategic Tools</h3>
					<p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground mt-2">Estimate your maintenance calories and daily expenditure.</p>
					<a href="/calculators/maintenance-calorie-calculator" class="button-primary w-full text-center text-xs mt-4 block">Maintenance Calculator</a>
				</div>

				<div class="surface border border-border p-5 rounded-2xl">
					<h3 class="font-bold text-sm text-foreground">Related Guides</h3>
					<div class="mt-3 space-y-2 text-xs">
						<a href="/guides/should-i-cut-or-bulk" class="block text-accent hover:underline">Cut or Bulk Matrix</a>
						<a href="/guides/body-recomposition" class="block text-accent hover:underline">Body Recomposition Science</a>
						<a href="/guides/protein-nutrition" class="block text-accent hover:underline font-semibold">Protein Intake Guide</a>
					</div>
				</div>
			</div>
		</div>
	</section>
</Layout>
